condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Accounting Software | Description :A computerized accounting software will be purchased and used for recordingand reporting purposes. | Due Date :30-Jun-2015

Finance Agreement :Competitive Fund Board | Description :The Recipient shall establish and, at all times during projectimplementation, maintain a Board to oversee activities under Part 1 of the project, which shall validate selected sub-projects andmonitor their results and impacts (Competitive Fund Board). | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Executive Secretariat | Description :The Recipient shall establish, and at all times during Projectimplementation, maintain an autonomous Executive Secretariat responsible for overall management of the Project (ExecutiveSecretariat). | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :External auditor | Description :The Recipient shall recruit (a) not later than five months after the EffectiveDate, the external auditor referred to in Section 4.09 (b) of the General conditions in accordance with section III of schedule 2of the financing agreement and pursuant to terms of reference satisfactory to the Association. | Due Date :29-May-2015

Finance Agreement :Internal auditor | Description :The Recipient shall recruit not later than three months after the EffectiveDate, an internal auditor, whose qualifications and experience and terms of reference shall be acceptable to the Association. | DueDate :30-Mar-2015

Finance Agreement :Safeguards | Description :The Recipient shall ensure that the Project is carried out in accordance with theprovisions of the Environmental and Social Management Framework (ESMF) in a manner satisfactory to the Association. | Frequency:CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Strategic Orientation Committee | Description :The Recipient shall, at all times during Project implementation,maintain a Strategic Orientation Committee to provide overall guidance for Project implementation. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Task force | Description :The Recipient shall establish and, at all times during project implementation,maintain a task force responsible for satisfactory execution and monitoring of planned activities under Part 3 of the project. |Frequency :CONTINUOUS
